It's a nice idea being able to see what your body could look like but it's 
not in anyway actually accurate. You need to be able to put in measurements 
for different body parts

The worst. Don't bother. Can't believe I spent money on this...it is 
worthless. Won't open with user name and password and when it opens through 
website link you lose your stored data. Wish I'd read the reviews before 
buying. Don't download even if it's free.

This app doesn't do much besides show you an avatar of what your body will 
sort of look like at varying weights. Not worth paying for. The idea is to 
update it as you lose weight and see your avatar 'lean out'. You know what 
else will show you that? A mirror. If this was a free app I wouldn't have 
such beef with it. But, in my opinion, it is not worth it. At all.
I paid put my info in several times once i exit it and go back in it reverts back to factory settings. So frustrated.

I created an account and logged in successfully. Entered all my stats etc. When I log in from the app, it keeps reverting back to the demo simulation and losing all my stats. Useless to me in terms of tracking progress.
